    "shortDescription": "Tree frogs can cling upside-down to glass without slipping, thanks to millions of tiny bumps on their toe pads that grip like a thousand little suction cups. They live in rainforests and gardens all over the world, calling out so loudly at night that they can drown out a conversation. Fun fact: Tree frogs don't drink water — they absorb it straight through their skin."
